2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 79
BY REPRESENTATIVE BUTLER
WILDLIFE & FISHERIES: Memorializes Congress and the United States Forest Service
to take such actions as are necessary to allow the use of dogs for hunting in the
Kisatchie National Forest
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress and the United States Forest Service to take such
3 actions as are necessary to allow the use of dogs for deer hunting in the Kisatchie
4 National Forest.
5 WHEREAS, the Kisatchie National Forest, spanning approximately six hundred four
6 thousand acres across seven parishes in central and northern Louisiana, provides valuable
7 wildlife habitat and public access for outdoor recreation, including hunting; and
8 WHEREAS, deer hunting is a long-standing tradition in Louisiana, and the use of
9 trained dogs for deer hunting has been an important part of that tradition in many rural
10 communities; and
11 WHEREAS, the use of dogs for hunting, training, and retrieval is a longstanding
12 tradition among hunters in Louisiana and throughout the United States; and
13 WHEREAS, properly managed hunting with dogs assists in the effective and humane
14 harvesting and recovery of game and reduces wounded-animal loss thus supporting wildlife
15 population objectives consistent with federal and state conservation laws; and
16 WHEREAS, current federal regulations and management policies of the United
17 States Forest Service restrict or prohibit the use of dogs for deer hunting in the Kisatchie
18 National Forest; and
